<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-1416] Make access of DecisionForest read() less restricted</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1416</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a use case I encounter in which a random forest model is passed to remote server over a REST API and is used for scoring the incoming requests in there. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In such a scenario it is highly inefficient to write the byte buffer received at the remote server on the filesystem and then use Mahout APIs to load the forest.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should be able to load the forest from the byte buffer received. This is useful in non-map-reduce usecases of classification like that mentioned above.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
