&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to &quot;public&quot; for what you are trying to achieve.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13899184" author="awmanoj" created="Wed, 12 Feb 2014 15:23:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=smarthi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;smarthi&quot;&gt;Suneel Marthi&lt;/a&gt; I agree with you. I considered that but was thinking of keeping the &quot;load forest &amp;amp; classify&quot; semantics of usage while proposing this patch. But now, I also think &quot;load&quot; would not be an appropriate name for a read from stream. Thanks for the comment.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
